<br>
I remember back in the day, I used to live in New Jersey. This was back when Christie Todd W. was still the governor, bless her little heart. They were doing a massive upgrade and reconstruction on the main North-South Interstate highway and the Jersey Turnpike. Problem is, particularly in the swampy bits, those roads are really the only way to get anyplace fast in the Armpit of America. A solution was needed, and Jersey came up with one. All construction would be done at night on third shift, like between 11 p.m. and 5 a.m., then they'd open as many lanes back up as possible so people could actually DRIVE on the fucking roads and go to work.<br>
<br>
Why can't we have that all over the country? Why the fuck does New York State (just for one example) have to shut down major roadways for fucking MONTHS at a time to only a single lane, 24/7, and re-route everyone through hell and back.  And can these assholes not estimate or plan ANYTHING eve close to reality? Last year they shut down a main city road right by where I live which everyone uses to get from the primarily residential section of town down to the business district where everyone works. (There's a railroad that runs through there and there's only two roads with convenient rail crossings to get back and forth.) The worked on it all fucking summer, which is ok because it needed work. Then fall comes and they decide that they fucked up on the estimates and the road wont' be done before the snow comes. So they shut down the operation and leave this major road closed all fucking winter. It finally opened back up this spring after 11 months. It was only supposed to be closed for three months.<br>
<br>
Now they're shutting down another one and it's November.<br>
<br>
Fucktards.<br>
<br>
Learn how to estimate fucking construction projects, and schedule the work when there's the least impact to the people actually using the services. Is that SOOOO fucking difficult to manage? This is the fucking municipal governments making these out-their-ass estimates. If a private contractor had to make a construction estimate and was that far off, HE'D STILL BE DOING TIME IN JAIL!<br>
<br>
Fuck's sakes. I NEED TO GET TO WORK IN THE MORNING, ASSWIPES! <p>Jaksomething<br>
